The programme includes reading and working on scientific literature (topic include, e.g. studying at university, special educational needs, assessment, 21st century skills), learning presentation techniques and  structure and parts of a research article and essay. Students will make a presentation based on a scientific article and write a research essay.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To enlarge students' vocabulary and develop language skills on C1 language level to work independently on scientific literature.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful completion of the course students will know the main terminology to understand education-related texts on C1 language level; discuss orally and in written educational topics; be able to paraphrase and summarise texts and know the requirements for referencing; know the structure of research articles; know the structure of a research essay; devise and write an essay according to the requirements; use suitable presentation techniques to deliver a presentation; analyse oral presentation of their peers.
